{{Portal|Anglicanism}}[[The Very Reverend|The Very Rev]] '''Cyril Evelyn Morton''' was an eminent [[Anglican]] [[priest]] in the first half of the 20th century.<ref>[http://lawfordherry.blogspot.com/2009/05/sir-alfred-herbert-and-st-barbaras.html Herry<U+2019>s Archives]</ref><br />He was born in 1885 and educated at [[Selwyn College, Cambridge]]. Ordained after a period of study at [[Ripon College Cuddesdon|Cuddesdon]] in 1908,<ref>"The Clergy List" London, Kelly<U+2019>s, 1913</ref> he began his ecclesiastical career with [[Curate|curacies]] in [[Hampstead]] and [[Roehampton]]. After this he held [[Vicar|incumbencies]] at [[Clifton On Dunsmore]] and [[Leamington Spa]]. In 1929 he became [[Dean (religion)|Sub-Dean]] of the [[Coventry Cathedral|Cathedral Church of St Michael, Coventry]]; and in 1931, following a change in the law, [[Coventry Cathedral|its]] first [[Provost (religion)|Provost]].<ref>''[[The Times]]'', Tuesday, Aug 18, 1931; pg. 13; Issue 45904; col C ''Ecclestastical News Coventry Cathedral''</ref> He died on 27 July 1932.<ref>''Provost Morton'' ''[[The Times]]'' Thursday, Jul 28, 1932; pg. 18; Issue 46197; col B</ref>
